ode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:35:The Q-Exec question in `deep-review.md` now offers all four executor kinds (A native, B cli-codex, C cli-copilot, D cli-claude-code) with the same brief per-CLI notes as the research command. Users get the same UX across both iterative skills so switching executors is identical regardless of which loop is active.\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/changelog/v1.3.0.0.md:78:| `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md` | Modified | Added explicit graph tool permissions |\n---\n-rw-r--r--@ 1 michelkerkmeester  staff  33338 Jun 27 13:20 /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.codex/agents/deep-review.md\n","metadata":{"output":"4:allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\n---\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:87:| `.opencode/commands/speckit/deep-review.md`                                                                              | Modified | Documented legal-stop, blocked-stop recovery, and optimizer thresholds for review operators |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:61:| `.opencode/commands/speckit/deep-review.md` | New review command |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/changelog/v1.3.2.0.md:66:The agent definition (`deep-review.md`) iteration skeleton was internally contradictory - different heading names than the reducer parser expected. Collapsed to one main fenced template matching the sections `reduce-state.cjs` actually consumes.\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/cha