{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783147822391,"sessionID":"ses_0d42abedcffewM196xEPACWSgW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_rilo1qst15mu_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/18--ux-hooks/goal-opencode-plugin.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/18--ux-hooks/goal-opencode-plugin.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Goal OpenCode plugin\"\n3: description: \"Local /goal OpenCode plugin that persists session objectives, injects active-goal context, exposes mk_goal tools, and documents restart and validation boundaries.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"goal opencode plugin\"\n6:   - \"mk-goal\"\n7:   - \"/goal command\"\n8:   - \"active_goal injection\"\n9:   - \"goalPrompt\"\n10: version: 3.7.0.1\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Goal OpenCode plugin\n14: \n15: This catalog entry maps the current `/goal` OpenCode plugin behavior to its implementation files, validation tests, and operator reference.\n16: \n17: <!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: The goal plugin gives OpenCode a session-level completion objective. Users call `/goal set <objective>` or `/goal set <objective> --budget N`, and the plugin persists the state, injects an active-goal block on each turn, and exposes tool-backed status, history, doctor/health, resume, and mutation operations.\n22: \n23: This feature is cataloged under UX hooks because it is a runtime-injection and operator-feedback surface. It is not part of the Spec Kit Memory MCP server and does not use a daemon CLI bridge.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n28: \n29: `.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js` is auto-loaded by OpenCode. It registers:\n30: \n31: - `experimental.chat.system.transform` to append `[active_goal:<goalId>]` when the session has an active goal.\n32: - `event` to restore goals, record message activity, track prompt blockers, verify on idle, and gate continuation.\n33: - `mk_goal` and `mk_goal_status` plugin tools for command routing and diagnostics.\n34: \n35: `.opencode/commands/goal_opencode.md` is intentionally thin. It parses `$ARGUMENTS`, calls exactly one plugin tool, and never reads or writes `.opencode/skills/.goal-state` directly.\n36: \n37: Stored state keeps both the raw sanitized `objective` and the deterministic `goalPrompt`. The raw objective is audit data; `goalPrompt` is the model-facing execution brief. Idle verification uses an injected `supervisorVerifier` when present; otherwise `MK_GOAL_VERIFIER=heuristic` applies a deterministic fail-closed verifier over the latest assistant evidence and goal objective. `MK_GOAL_VERIFIER=llm` opts into `ctx.client.session.promptAsync` semantic verdicts. Status output includes verifier provenance as `verifier_source` with `injected`, `default-heuristic`, or `default-llm` when a verdict has run. Autonomy is disabled unless `MK_GOAL_AUTONOMY=active` or smoke-tested with `MK_GOAL_AUTONOMY=smoke`. `MK_GOAL_MAX_AUTO_TURNS` and `MK_GOAL_MAX_WALL_MS` tune the guarded continuation caps; status output includes `remaining_auto_turns`, `remaining_wall_ms`, and `provider_retry_after_ms`.\n38: \n39: State does not grow unboundedly: on `session.deleted` the goal-state file is archived then pruned past a retention window, `/goal history` lists archived records read-only, and a throttled sweep on `session.created` archives orphaned active-state files past their own age threshold. `/goal doctor` and `/goal health` report active/archive counts, log sizes, last sweep time, and orphan candidates. `/goal resume` reactivates only `paused` or `usage_limited` goals. See `references/hooks/goal_plugin.md` for the retention/sweep env vars and the `store_health`/`mutation` output fields.\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ## 3. SOURCE FILES\n44: \n45: ### Implementation\n46: \n47: | File | Layer | Role |\n48: |------|-------|------|\n49: | `.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js` | OpenCode plugin | State, injection, lifecycle, verifier, continuation gates, and plugin tools. |\n50: | `.opencode/commands/goal_opencode.md` | Slash command | Thin `/goal` router for `set`, `show`, `history`, `doctor`, `health`, `clear`, `complete`, `pause`, and `resume`. |\n51: | `.opencode/skills/.goal-state/` | Runtime state | Per-session JSON goal records and bounded debug logs. |\n52: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/goal_plugin.md` | Operator reference | Contract, env vars, boundaries, verification, and restart guidance. |\n53: \n54: ### Validation And Tests\n55: \n56: | File | Type | Role |\n57: |---|---|---|\n58: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-state.test.cjs` | Automated test | State, generated prompt fields, injection, caps, and sanitization. |\n59: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-tool-path.test.cjs` | Automated test | Plugin tool context persistence and status output. |\n60: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-export-contract.test.cjs` | Automated test | Export contract. |\n61: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-capabilities.test.cjs` | Automated test | History, doctor/health, resume, budget, env caps, provider-limit detection, and retry-after recovery. |\n62: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-lifecycle.test.cjs` | Automated test | Event/lifecycle behavior. |\n63: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-supervisor.test.cjs` | Automated test | Injected verifier precedence, default heuristic positive/negative matrix, LLM verifier mode, provenance, and evidence redaction. |\n64: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-continuation.test.cjs` | Automated test | Guarded continuation decisions. |\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n69: \n70: - Group: UX Hooks\n71: - Canonical catalog source: `feature_catalog.md`\n72: - Feature file path: `18--ux-hooks/goal-opencode-plugin.md`\n73: - Related reference: `references/hooks/goal_plugin.md`\n\n(End of file - total 73 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Goal OpenCode plugin\"\ndescription: \"Local /goal OpenCode plugin that persists session objectives, injects active-goal context, exposes mk_goal tools, and documents restart and validation boundaries.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"goal opencode plugin\"\n  - \"mk-goal\"\n  - \"/goal command\"\n  - \"active_goal injection\"\n  - \"goalPrompt\"\nversion: 3.7.0.1\n---\n\n# Goal OpenCode plugin\n\nThis catalog entry maps the current `/goal` OpenCode plugin behavior to its implementation files, validation tests, and operator reference.\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/18--ux-hooks/goal-opencode-plugin.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Goal OpenCode plugin\"\ndescription: \"Local /goal OpenCode plugin that persists session objectives, injects active-goal context, exposes mk_goal tools, and documents restart and validation boundaries.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"goal opencode plugin\"\n  - \"mk-goal\"\n  - \"/goal command\"\n  - \"active_goal injection\"\n  - \"goalPrompt\"\nversion: 3.7.0.1\n---\n\n# Goal OpenCode plugin\n\nThis catalog entry maps the current `/goal` OpenCode plugin behavior to its implementation files, validation tests, and operator reference.\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe goal plugin gives OpenCode a session-level completion objective. Users call `/goal set <objective>` or `/goal set <objective> --budget N`, and the plugin persists the state, injects an active-goal block on each turn, and exposes tool-backed status, history, doctor/health, resume, and mutation operations.\n\nThis feature is cataloged under UX hooks because it is a runtime-injection and operator-feedback surface. It is not part of the Spec Kit Memory MCP server and does not use a daemon CLI bridge.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n\n`.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js` is auto-loaded by OpenCode. It registers:\n\n- `experimental.chat.system.transform` to append `[active_goal:<goalId>]` when the session has an active goal.\n- `event` to restore goals, record message activity, track prompt blockers, verify on idle, and gate continuation.\n- `mk_goal` and `mk_goal_status` plugin tools for command routing and diagnostics.\n\n`.opencode/commands/goal_opencode.md` is intentionally thin. It parses `$ARGUMENTS`, calls exactly one plugin tool, and never reads or writes `.opencode/skills/.goal-state` directly.\n\nStored state keeps both the raw sanitized `objective` and the deterministic `goalPrompt`. The raw objective is audit data; `goalPrompt` is the model-facing execution brief. Idle verification uses an injected `supervisorVerifier` when present; otherwise `MK_GOAL_VERIFIER=heuristic` applies a deterministic fail-closed verifier over the latest assistant evidence and goal objective. `MK_GOAL_VERIFIER=llm` opts into `ctx.client.session.promptAsync` semantic verdicts. Status output includes verifier provenance as `verifier_source` with `injected`, `default-heuristic`, or `default-llm` when a verdict has run. Autonomy is disabled unless `MK_GOAL_AUTONOMY=active` or smoke-tested with `MK_GOAL_AUTONOMY=smoke`. `MK_GOAL_MAX_AUTO_TURNS` and `MK_GOAL_MAX_WALL_MS` tune the guarded continuation caps; status output includes `remaining_auto_turns`, `remaining_wall_ms`, and `provider_retry_after_ms`.\n\nState does not grow unboundedly: on `session.deleted` the goal-state file is archived then pruned past a retention window, `/goal history` lists archived records read-only, and a throttled sweep on `session.created` archives orphaned active-state files past their own age threshold. `/goal doctor` and `/goal health` report active/archive counts, log sizes, last sweep time, and orphan candidates. `/goal resume` reactivates only `paused` or `usage_limited` goals. See `references/hooks/goal_plugin.md` for the retention/sweep env vars and the `store_health`/`mutation` output fields.\n\n---\n\n## 3. SOURCE FILES\n\n### Implementation\n\n| File | Layer | Role |\n|------|-------|------|\n| `.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js` | OpenCode plugin | State, injection, lifecycle, verifier, continuation gates, and plugin tools. |\n| `.opencode/commands/goal_opencode.md` | Slash command | Thin `/goal` router for `set`, `show`, `history`, `doctor`, `health`, `clear`, `complete`, `pause`, and `resume`. |\n| `.opencode/skills/.goal-state/` | Runtime state | Per-session JSON goal records and bounded debug logs. |\n| `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/goal_plugin.md` | Operator reference | Contract, env vars, boundaries, verification, and restart guidance. |\n\n### Validation And Tests\n\n| File | Type | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-state.test.cjs` | Automated test | State, generated prompt fields, injection, caps, and sanitization. |\n| `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-tool-path.test.cjs` | Automated test | Plugin tool context persistence and status output. |\n| `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-export-contract.test.cjs` | Automated test | Export contract. |\n| `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-capabilities.test.cjs` | Automated test | History, doctor/health, resume, budget, env caps, provider-limit detection, and retry-after recovery. |\n| `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-lifecycle.test.cjs` | Automated test | Event/lifecycle behavior. |\n| `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-supervisor.test.cjs` | Automated test | Injected verifier precedence, default heuristic positive/negative matrix, LLM verifier mode, provenance, and evidence redaction. |\n| `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-goal-continuation.test.cjs` | Automated test | Guarded continuation decisions. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n\n- Group: UX Hooks\n- Canonical catalog source: `feature_catalog.md`\n- Feature file path: `18--ux-hooks/goal-opencode-plugin.md`\n- Related reference: `references/hooks/goal_plugin.md`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":73,"totalLines":73,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/18--ux-hooks/goal-opencode-plugin.md","time":{"start":1783147822384,"end":1783147822390}},"id":"prt_f2be47a4a001abyYVyTiZXGmJB","sessionID":"ses_0d42abedcffewM196xEPACWSgW","messageID":"msg_f2be46cc60014JAqEYZXddHY9Y"}}
